Introduction: - PM SHRI (PM Schools for Rising India), a centrally sponsored scheme, is being implemented in the state since the year 2022-23. The expenditure on the scheme is borne by the Central Government and the State Government in the ratio 60:40 respectively. Reference No. The Central Government, by order 1B2, provides for the Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan component.

The third instalment of this current financial year has been deposited in the Consolidated Fund of the State. The proposal for devolution of this fund and its corresponding State share is referred to Reference No. Section 3 has been submitted to the government.
A proposal to approve it was under consideration of the government.
The Government's Decisions:

For implementation of the Centrally Sponsored Scheme of PM SHRI (PM Schools for Rising India), the Central Government has released the third instalment of Central share of Rs. 9,40,74, 000 / - (Characters Rs. nine crore forty lakh seventy four thousand) and the corresponding State share of Rs. 6,27,16, 000 / - (Characters Rs. Six crore twenty-seven lakh sixteen thousand) totaling to Rs. 15,67,90, 000 / - (Characters Rs. Fifteen crore sixty six lakh ninety thousand) is being sanctioned to the State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education, Charni Road, Mumbai as follows:

6. The State Project Director, Maharashtra Primary Education Council, Mumbai, while spending the said provision, issued the Financial Rules in the Maharashtra Budget Manual, Fiscal Rights Manual as well as the Circular B in the context of the Finance Department in the context of the Tribal Development Department. Strictly follow the directions given in the Government Circular dated 18.10.2024. It should be ensured that the funds are spent in this year as per the approved plan in line with the existing government policy on expenditure.

The Under Secretary / Cell Officer (Cash / Accounts Branch), School Education & Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai is being declared as the Drawing & Disbursing Officer and Joint / Deputy Secretary, School Education Sports Department, Mantralaya, Mumbai as the Controlling Officer for the collection and disbursement of these funds.

The concerned Drawing and Disbursing Officer should withdraw the funds from the treasury and deposit them in the concerned back account under the State Project Director, Maharashtra Council of Elementary Education.

8. Report of expenditure incurred from the provision made available under the head Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan, Certificate of Fund Utilization, material objectives achieved by title / sub-heading, etc.
The information should be sent to the Tribal Development Department B School Education Department by the 10th of every month by the concerned zonal officer without fail.

9. Tribal field sub-plans, Scheduled Tribe sub-plans shall ensure that the expenditure made in the external sector is recorded separately. So that the government can keep a check on the SSAA expenditure outside the sub-plan area.

10. From the provision made available under the Scheduled Tribes Special Component Programme, individual benefit schemes shall be taken up in the area as per the scheme framework and only individual benefit schemes shall be taken up in the area outside the Scheduled Tribes Sub-Plan.
